parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the brake pedal to feel soft or spongy, leading to delayed or incomplete stopping, which can result in accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floor
the brake pedal has a delayed response
the brake pedal has a hissing sound
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.

the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floor
the brake pedal has a delayed response
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning HVAC system can cause the air conditioning and heating to malfunction, leading to uncomfortable temperatures and foggy windows, which can impair visibility and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The air conditioning and heating do not function properly
the buttons on the HVAC system turn on without being touched
the windows fog up
and the system switches between air conditioning and heating modes randomly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door ajar sensor can cause the doors to not latch properly, leading to safety issues, such as the inability to lock the doors while driving, and can also trigger the alarm system.
symptoms: The door ajar warning light stays on even when the doors are closed
the doors do not latch properly
the alarm system is triggered
and the dome lights stay on while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal is hard to push
the brake booster fails
and the brakes barely work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sensitivity of the electronic key fob can cause the windows to roll down, the sunroof to open, and the alarm system to trigger, leading to inconvenience and potential safety issues.
symptoms: The electronic key fob is too sensitive
causing the windows to roll down
the sunroof to open
and the alarm system to trigger.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling of the engine and loss of power can cause the vehicle to become stranded, leading to safety issues and inconvenience.
symptoms: The engine stalls
the vehicle loses power
and the dashboard control panel blacks out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty door ajar warning system can cause unnecessary stress and distraction while driving, and may lead to battery drain and other issues.
symptoms: The door ajar warning light remains on despite all doors being closed securely
interior lights stay on
and entry alarm goes off at any hour.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the brake pedal to travel to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
excessive pumping is needed to build pressure on the brake pads.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power brake booster can cause the brake pedal to travel to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
excessive pumping is needed to build pressure on the brake pads.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty transmission can cause the vehicle to slip out of park and roll away, which can lead to accidents or property damage.
symptoms: The vehicle slips out of park and rolls away
especially on uneven pavement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The exhaust leak into the cabin can cause health problems, such as headaches, burning eyes, nausea, and disorientation, and can make the vehicle unsafe to drive.
symptoms: Exhaust smell is noticeable in the cabin
especially during hard acceleration
and symptoms develop within thirty minutes of driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle stalling and going into limp mode can cause loss of control and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly stops responding and goes into limp mode
especially while driving at high speeds.
